│ The `DomTreeUpdater::deleteBB` function ensures that the basic block being deleted is      │
│ validated first using `validateDeleteBB`. If the update strategy is `Lazy`, the block is   │
│ added to a set of deleted blocks (`DeletedBBs`) and not immediately deleted. Otherwise,    │
│ the block is erased from the dominator tree and then removed from the parent.              │
│                                                                                            │
│ The issue arises because `validateDeleteBB` asserts that the block has no predecessors,    │
│ but the IPSCCP pass does not ensure this condition before calling `deleteBB`.              │
│                                                                                            │
│ To address this, we need to modify the IPSCCP pass to ensure that all predecessors of a    │
